&gt; If it doesn&#39;t exist, how can you POST into it. 404 or 410 IMO.

404 just means no representations are available (source), and doesn&#39;t
necessarily mean that there isn&#39;t any processing logic there (sink).
Most HTML form processors are this kind of resource; try invoking GET
on the &quot;action URI&quot; of an arbitrary form.

Of course, it&#39;s possible and useful (IME) to be able to use GET to
represent the state of the sink, but it&#39;s not required.

